        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(diffs): continue after card hydration errors",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Keep hydrating remaining diff cards when one card fails during `FileDiff` construction or `hydrate()`.\n- Log a per-card warning instead of letting one failure reject the whole viewer hydration path.\n- Add jsdom coverage proving a later card still hydrates after the first card throws.\n\nFixes #83914\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: `hydrateViewer` previously ran each `.oc-diff-card` hydration in one unguarded loop. If one card threw during `FileDiff` construction, `hydrate()`, or state application, the exception propagated out of `hydrateViewer` and later cards were not hydrated.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on macOS, Node.js v22.22.0, branch `publish/diffs-continue-after-card-hydration-error-83914`, using jsdom plus the real `extensions/diffs/src/viewer-client.ts` hydration loop under the repo's Vitest wrapper.\n\nExact steps or command run after fix:\n\n```console\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/diffs/src/viewer-client.test.ts\n$ git diff --check\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: Targeted test output:\n\n```console\n✓ extension-diffs ../../extensions/diffs/src/viewer-client.test.ts (1 test) 77ms\n\nTest Files 1 passed (1)\nTests 1 passed (1)\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The regression test renders two diff cards, makes the first `hydrate()` call throw, then verifies `hydrate()` is still invoked for the second card, one controller is registered for the successful card, and the page-level `openclawDiffsError` flag is not set by the per-card failure.\n\nWhat was not tested: I did not run a full browser artifact build or open the generated viewer HTML in a real browser; the targeted jsdom test exercises the failing per-card hydration seam directly.\n\n## Test plan\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/diffs/src/viewer-client.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n",
